==Trivia==
*In the comics, Willis Stryker was a childhood friend of [[Carl Lucas]] and [[Shades]]. Jealous that [[Reva Connors]] loved Lucas, Stryker framed him for hiding stolen [[Maggia]]'s drugs in his house. Maggia then tried to kill Stryker but ended up killing Connors instead.
**In the comics, Cage had a brother named '''James Lucas, Jr.''', codenamed '''Coldfire''', who underwent an experiment led by [[Karl Malus]] to gain superpowers in order to fight Cage, as he hated him.

==Behind the Scenes==
*According to ''[[Luke Cage (TV series)|Luke Cage]]'' creator and showrunner [[Cheo Hodari Coker]], Diamondback's planned arc for the series had been altered when the writers of ''[[Jessica Jones (TV series)|Jessica Jones]]'' [[Jessica Jones (TV series)/Season One|season one]] "departed from [comic] canon" by having [[Kilgrave]] kill [[Reva Connors]]. Given the reception Diamondback received from fans, Coker admitted that if he could change one thing regarding the series, he would retool Diamondback's character,<ref>[https://x.com/cheo_coker/status/1282853805952884736 Cheo Hodari Coker on Twitter - July 14, 2020]</ref> stating that he did not feel they got the tone of the character right until the [[Now You're Mine|third last episode]].<ref>[https://x.com/cheo_coker/status/1496549769287958528 Cheo Hodari Coker on Twitter - February 23, 2022]</ref>
*[[Califf Guzman]] was a stunt double for [[Erik LaRay Harvey]] in the role of Diamondback.
*[[Nadir Hasan]] was a stand-in for [[Jared Kemp]] in the role of Diamondback.

